        "en": "Capital of Roman Lusitania, Mérida contains more intact Roman monuments than any Spanish city outside Rome. The Theatre of Augustus (16 BC) still hosts summer performances. The amphitheatre, circus, aqueducts, and Temple of Diana form a remarkable UNESCO World Heritage ensemble. The National Museum of Roman Art, designed by Rafael Moneo, is world-class. The Roman bridge over the Guadiana, with 60 arches, is one of the longest surviving in the world.",
